-- Oil hits new record of $84.22 a barrel
-- 
-- Mon Oct 15, 2007 5:33am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/10/15/us-oil-record-wti-idUSWLA134220071015

 

 LONDON  (Reuters) - U.S. NYMEX crude oil futures hit a new record high of $84.22 a barrel on Monday, supported by worries of tension between Turkey and Iraq and winter supply worries. 

 U.S. crude was up 48 cents a barrel at $84.17 by 5:04 a.m. EDT.